result.execSummary:
The defendant Steven J. Trout was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant is entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges. Sentence to commence forthwith.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

Case called @ 3:29 p.m. Defendant Steven J. Trout in court with attorney Katherine Seifert.  Defendant Steven J. Trout in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Upon motion of the State the Court amends Ct 1 to Misdemeanor Battery contrary to Wis Stat 940.19(1), 939.62(1)(a). Domestic Abuse enhancer stricken by the Court. Plea: NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Ct 2 - DRI. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Atty Seifert. Statement by DE. Court orders: 9 mos WC Jail - Huber, GT, 52 days CFTS - Sentence to commence forthwith, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge. Case Called @ 1:17 PM: Defendant Steven J. Trout in court with attorney Katherine Seifert, both appearing in person.   Defendant Steven J. Trout in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Per Atty Seifert, Def is prepared to waive Pre-Lim at this time - offers extended by the State.   Preliminary Hearing and Time Limits discussed.  Written waiver provided by counsel.  Defendant wishes to waive preliminary hearing in its entirety.  Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing.  Def BOT.  ARGN to proceed.  INFO Filed - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.   NGP received and entered.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Atty Seifert argues for bond modification - Def is unable to post any cash for release. The Court respectfully declines to order any bond modification at this time.  Issue may be reconsidered if input is received from victim.  Status conference scheduled for April 1, 2016 at 03:05 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 1:04 PM:  Defendant Steven J. Trout in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi, both appearing via video.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
